## 1. GitHub Actions Secrets

Set repository secrets:
- `CONFIG_API_URL`: Your PythonAnywhere config API URL, e.g. `https://your-domain.pythonanywhere.com/api/config`
- `LINE_TOKEN`: Your LINE Messaging API channel access token

Workflow file: `.github/workflows/check_stock.yml`

## 1.1 Config API fields for long-term drop trigger

In your config API response JSON, you can add:

- `long_term_drop.days`: lookback days for long-term drop check (default `60`)
- `long_term_drop.drop_percent`: drop threshold percent (default `10`)

Example:

```json
{
	"long_term_drop": {
		"days": 60,
		"drop_percent": 10
	},
	"rules": [
		{"symbol": "VOO", "x_days": 5, "y_percent": 5}
	]
}
```

If these fields are missing or invalid, code falls back to `60` and `10`.

## 2. Test checker script locally

```bash
set CONFIG_API_URL=https://your-domain.pythonanywhere.com/api/config
set LINE_TOKEN=your_line_token
python script/check_stock.py
```


## 3. Run Test case

./run_test.ps1 => generate report coverage_summary.txt and coverage.xml (for vs code Watch)